Caption:
Piertotum Locomotor can be used to charm anything the caster wants, so long as it is an inanimate object. Before Professor McGonagall used it to defend the school against Voldemort's army, it was seen doing relatively mundane things. Molly Weasley was known to use the spell to animate her dustpan to pick up spilled potatoes or anything else she needed to be done around the house. The spell's uses are nearly limitless, making it one of the most powerful charms in the Harry Potter universe. â

Form III, also known as Soresu was developed around the time blaster technology became prominent throughout the galaxy. It was initially designed to counter the long-range threat, as Forms I and II were incapable of adapting to incoming blaster fire. Because of this, Soresu relies heavily on the lightsaber blade's ability to block blaster fire.â 
â 
Contrary to appearances in the films, it takes great skill to deflect those inbound bolts at an enemy. Such accuracy takes years to master, and Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi was arguably the best during the latter years of the Republic. Form III is primarily defensive, as it aids in blocking attacks. That said, it incorporates powerful parry techniques capable of bringing the fight to the aggressor.â
